, to the militarized masculinities of mass shooters-Military Waste reveals the unexpected and open-ended relationships that non-combatants on the home front form with a nation permanently ready for war.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aMilitary suppliesxEnvironmental aspects. 0aMilitary suppliesxSocial aspects. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh  aabandoned military bases.  aaggression.  aaircraft.  aassault weapons.  acivilians.  acontrol.  aenvironment.  aexcess planes.  afighter planes.  agender.  agovernment spending.  ahome front.  amasculinity.  amass shooters.  amilitarization.  amilitary bases.  amilitary grade weapons.  amilitary industrial complex.  amilitary junk.  amilitary spending.  amilitary technology.  amilitary.  anoncombatants.  anonfiction.  apentagon.  apollution.  apower.  ascience.  aships.  asocial history.  asoldiers.  aspace debris.  atechnology.  aviolence.  awar preparation.  awar.  awarfare.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520974128zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520974128423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520974128.jpg  a978-3-11-069041-5  UC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11